---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AztecPattern from '../../components/decorative/AztecPattern.astro';
import GeometricBorder from '../../components/decorative/GeometricBorder.astro';
import CircuitFeather from '../../components/CircuitFeather.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Silas Hale's Journey"
  description="Follow the story of Silas Hale, a Nextla Agent navigating the complexities of Mirador's attention economy."
>
  <!-- Hero Section with Pattern -->
  <div class="relative py-24 bg-primary-800">
    <AztecPattern pattern="flow" opacity={0.15} color="#A63D2F" className="hero-pattern" />
    
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8 relative z-10">
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-4 mb-6">
        <CircuitFeather severity="moderate" size="lg" animated={true} />
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-white tracking-wider">Silas Hale's Journey</h1>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-200 max-w-2xl">
        The story of a Nextla Agent tasked with monitoring capability compliance across city-states
        while navigating personal and ethical dilemmas.
      </p>
      <GeometricBorder type="horizontal" color="accent" className="mt-8 w-32" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <div class="bg-primary-900 py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold mb-6 text-accent-400">The Agent</h2>
        <GeometricBorder type="horizontal" color="accent" className="mb-6 w-24" />
        
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 text-neutral-200">
          Silas Hale never wanted to be a Nextla Agent. After a promising career as an architect in Arcadia,
          a severe capability violation left parts of his design firm's district in ruins. The manifestation
          was one of the worst recorded—buildings reconfigured themselves while people were inside them.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 text-neutral-200">
          When Toltec investigators discovered that Silas had unconsciously detected warning signs months before the incident,
          they recruited him for his unique sensitivity to capability imbalances. Five years later, he's become one of their
          most effective field agents, though he remains conflicted about his role.
        </p>
        
        <div class="bg-primary-800 p-8 rounded-lg border border-primary-700 my-12 relative overflow-hidden">
          <AztecPattern pattern="flow" opacity={0.1} color="#A63D2F" className="quote-pattern" />
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
              <CircuitFeather severity="moderate" size="md" className="mr-4" />
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-medium text-accent-400">From Silas's Field Notes</h3>
            </div>
            <blockquote class="text-lg italic text-neutral-200 pl-6 border-l-4 border-accent-500">
              "I've started seeing them even without my field equipment—the subtle distortions in space that precede a manifestation. It's like my brain has rewired itself to detect capability imbalances. Toltec says this makes me valuable. Sometimes I wonder if it's actually driving me insane."
            </blockquote>
            <p class="text-right text-sm text-neutral-400 mt-4">— Personal Log, Day 1,247</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold mb-6 mt-12 text-accent-400">Reconciliation Work</h2>
        <GeometricBorder type="horizontal" color="accent" className="mb-6 w-24" />
        
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 text-neutral-200">
          As a Reconciliation Agent, Silas travels between city-states, investigating potential capability violations
          and documenting manifestations. His official role is to ensure compliance with licensing agreements, but
          he often finds himself mediating disputes between city officials and Toltec representatives.
        </p>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-primary-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-700">
            <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-accent-400">Detection</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-300">Using specialized equipment and his own heightened sensitivity, Silas monitors for early signs of capability imbalance.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-700">
            <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-accent-400">Assessment</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-300">Evaluating the severity of manifestations and determining the specific capability violations that caused them.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-700">
            <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-accent-400">Mediation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-300">Negotiating compliance terms between city-states and Toltec, often weighing competing priorities and needs.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-700">
            <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-accent-400">Enforcement</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-300">When necessary, implementing capability restrictions or initiating emergency reconciliation protocols.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold mb-6 mt-12 text-accent-400">Personal Conflicts</h2>
        <GeometricBorder type="horizontal" color="accent" className="mb-6 w-24" />
        
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 text-neutral-200">
          Silas increasingly questions the ethics of Toltec's capability licensing model. His interactions with
          resistance groups, particularly in the Outland territories, have exposed him to alternative perspectives on
          how capabilities should be managed and distributed.
        </p>
        
        <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-primary-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-700">
            <div class="flex items-center">
              <CircuitFeather severity="minor" size="sm" className="mr-3" />
              <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-accent-400">Professional Duty</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-300 mt-2">
              Silas believes in preventing the dangerous consequences of unchecked capability usage, having witnessed the destruction firsthand.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-700">
            <div class="flex items-center">
              <CircuitFeather severity="moderate" size="sm" className="mr-3" />
              <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-accent-400">Moral Doubts</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-300 mt-2">
              He questions whether Toltec's monopolistic control is creating unnecessary suffering, especially in poorer regions that cannot afford proper licensing.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-700">
            <div class="flex items-center">
              <CircuitFeather severity="severe" size="sm" className="mr-3" />
              <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-accent-400">Personal Connections</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-300 mt-2">
              His friendship with Enrique, a resistance leader, and developing relationship with Victoria Ford, a social critic, pull him toward more radical perspectives.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-primary-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-700">
            <div class="flex items-center">
              <CircuitFeather severity="critical" size="sm" className="mr-3" />
              <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg text-accent-400">Growing Suspicions</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="text-neutral-300 mt-2">
              Silas has begun uncovering evidence that manifestations might not be natural consequences of imbalance, but deliberately engineered control mechanisms.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-primary-700 p-8 rounded-lg mt-12 border border-primary-600 shadow-lg relative overflow-hidden">
          <AztecPattern pattern="tribute" opacity={0.08} color="#FFC107" className="cta-pattern" />
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mb-4 text-white">Explore Technical Documentation</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-200 mb-6">
              Understand the capabilities, entitlements, and reconciliation systems that form the backbone of Mirador's technology infrastructure.
            </p>
            <a href="/technical/reconciliation?mode=technical" class="inline-block bg-accent-500 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded hover:bg-accent-600 transition-colors shadow-md">
              View Technical Details
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout> 